---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "Tracker Season 3: Cast Additions, Release Date, and Everything You Need to Know",
  description: "When does Tracker season 3 come out? Who are the new cast members? Discover the essential facts about Colter Shaw's next chapter before it airs.",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When does Tracker Season 3 premiere?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Tracker Season 3 officially premiered on October 19, 2025."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Who are the new cast members in Tracker Season 3?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "New cast members joining in Season 3 include Cassady McClincy Zhang as Melanie \"Mel\" Day, Mark Engelhardt as Emile Lang, Kathleen Robertson as Maxine, Erica Durance as Laura, and David Ramsey as Baxter."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Did Eric Graise and Abby McEnany leave the show?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, it was reported in July 2025 that Eric Graise (Bobby) and Abby McEnany (Velma) departed the series ahead of the third season."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where is Tracker Season 3 filmed?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Tracker is filmed in British Columbia, Canada, specifically on location around the Vancouver metro area and at Vancouver Film Studios."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is there a Tracker Season 4?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, CBS officially renewed the series for a fourth season on January 22, 2026."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="siliconbased"
  title={meta.title}
  description={meta.description}
  canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/tracker-season-3"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Tracker Season 3: The Ultimate Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Release dates, cast changes, and everything you need to know about the next chapter of Colter Shaw's journey.</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <p>
        The hit action drama television series <em>Tracker</em>, based on Jeffery Deaver's 2019 novel <em>The Never Game</em>, has captivated audiences with the adventures of Colter Shaw (played by Justin Hartley).
        As a skilled survivalist and tracker, Shaw travels the country helping private citizens and law enforcement solve mysteries and locate missing persons in exchange for reward money.
        With the series moving into its third season, there are massive shifts in the narrative, cast, and production that fans need to know about.
      </p>

      <h2>When Did Tracker Season 3 Air?</h2>
      <p>
        For fans eagerly anticipating the return of the CBS drama, the wait ended in late 2025. Following the successful run of Season 2 (which premiered on October 13, 2024), the series was officially renewed for a third season on February 20, 2025.
        <strong>Tracker Season 3 premiered on October 19, 2025.</strong>
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Key Timeline Detail:</strong> Filming for the third season commenced in the Vancouver metro area on July 17, 2025, and is scheduled to conclude on April 17, 2026. This extensive production schedule highlights the expanding scope and complexity of the show's episodic locations.
      </div>

      <h2>Major Cast Changes and New Faces</h2>
      <p>
        Television shows often undergo cast rotations as storylines evolve, and <em>Tracker</em> is no exception. Season 3 brings some of the most significant cast shakeups in the show's history.
      </p>

      <h3>Departures Ahead of Season 3</h3>
      <p>
        The support team that fans grew to love in the first two seasons looks very different now. In July 2025, it was announced that two principal cast members were leaving the series:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Eric Graise (Bobby Exley):</strong> The brilliant hacker who assisted Colter from a technical standpoint. (His role was gradually filled by Chris Lee's character, Randy, starting in Season 2).</li>
        <li><strong>Abby McEnany (Velma Bruin):</strong> Colter's handler who worked alongside Teddi (Robin Weigert, who departed after Season 1).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>New Arrivals and Guest Stars</h3>
      <p>
        To fill the void and introduce new dynamics, Season 3 welcomes several intriguing characters:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cassady McClincy Zhang as Melanie "Mel" Day:</strong> Reenie's new assistant.</li>
        <li><strong>Mark Engelhardt as Emile Lang:</strong> Introduced as a recurring character, Lang is a highly dangerous contract killer.</li>
        <li><strong>Kathleen Robertson as Maxine:</strong> Joined in a recurring capacity in December 2025.</li>
        <li><strong>Guest Stars:</strong> In January 2026, it was reported that fan-favorites Erica Durance (Laura) and David Ramsey (Baxter) are set to guest star in a highly anticipated episode.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Evolution of a Procedural</h3>
        <p>
          The transitions occurring in <em>Tracker Season 3</em> are vital for the show's longevity. By rotating the supporting cast, the writers force Colter Shaw out of his comfort zone. Losing his established handlers means Shaw must rely on new alliances and face even higher stakes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Furthermore, the introduction of a recurring antagonist like contract killer Emile Lang signals a shift towards serialized storytelling. Rather than strictly episodic "case-of-the-week" formats, the show is building longer narrative arcs that reward dedicated viewers. The massive success of these changes is evident: CBS already renewed the series for a fourth season on January 22, 2026.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        If you are interested in tracking timelines and growth metrics in other areas of life, you might also find our <a href="/baby-list">Baby Growth Chart Calculator</a> useful for understanding pediatric percentiles. Or, if you are looking to skip filler episodes in another popular show, check out our <a href="/bleach-filler-list">Bleach Filler List</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <details>
        <summary>When does Tracker Season 3 premiere?</summary>
        <p>Tracker Season 3 officially premiered on October 19, 2025, on CBS.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Who are the new cast members in Tracker Season 3?</summary>
        <p>New cast members joining in Season 3 include Cassady McClincy Zhang as Melanie "Mel" Day, Mark Engelhardt as Emile Lang, Kathleen Robertson as Maxine, Erica Durance as Laura, and David Ramsey as Baxter.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Did Eric Graise and Abby McEnany leave the show?</summary>
        <p>Yes, it was reported in July 2025 that Eric Graise (Bobby Exley) and Abby McEnany (Velma Bruin) departed the series ahead of the third season.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Where is Tracker Season 3 filmed?</summary>
        <p>Like previous seasons, Tracker is filmed in British Columbia, Canada, specifically on location around the Vancouver metro area and at Vancouver Film Studios.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Is there a Tracker Season 4?</summary>
        <p>Yes, due to the show's continued success, CBS officially renewed the series for a fourth season on January 22, 2026.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .callout { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color); padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; color: var(--text-primary); }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    p { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.6; }
    ul { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    h2, h3 { color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
